  "ai_usage": "Use for news tickers, stock tapes, and retro homages — never the deprecated <marquee> tag. Wrap content in an overflow:hidden track; the inner element animates translateX(0 → -100%). Duplicate the content inline for a seamless loop. PROVIDE A PAUSE (hover/focus + a real button in production) and disable under prefers-reduced-motion for accessibility.",
  "path": "effects/retro-web/marquee-scroll.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>CSS Marquee (modern &lt;marquee&gt;)</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"marquee-scroll\",\n    \"title\": \"CSS Marquee\",\n    \"summary\": \"A modern, accessible replacement for the deprecated <marquee> tag using CSS animation.\",\n    \"description\": \"Recreates the scrolling-ticker look of the old <marquee> element with a translateX keyframe, pausing on hover and under reduced-motion — without the deprecated tag.\",\n    \"theme\": \"retro-web\",\n    \"categories\": [\"retro\", \"ticker\", \"animation\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"marquee\", \"scroll\", \"ticker\", \"90s\", \"news\", \"deprecated-tag\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"1990s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All browsers (the CSS version). The original <marquee> tag is deprecated — do not use it.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"Single translateX loop; cheap. Duplicate the content for a seamless infinite ticker.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Auto-scrolling text is a WCAG concern: provide a pause control (this pauses on hover/focus) and STOP entirely under prefers-reduced-motion. Keep the full text in the DOM for screen readers.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--speed\", \"description\": \"Scroll duration\", \"default\": \"12s\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Right-to-left vs left-to-right\", \"Vertical news ticker\", \"Seamless loop by duplicating content\"],\n    \"related\": [\"rainbow-text\", \"blink-text\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Use for news tickers, stock tapes, and retro homages — never the deprecated <marquee> tag. Wrap content in an overflow:hidden track; the inner element animates translateX(0 → -100%). Duplicate the content inline for a seamless loop. PROVIDE A PAUSE (hover/focus + a real button in production) and disable under prefers-reduced-motion for accessibility.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root { --speed: 12s; }\n    html, body { height: 100%; margin: 0; }\n    body { display: grid; place-items: center; background: #000080; font-family: \"Comic Sans MS\", \"Trebuchet MS\", sans-serif; }\n    .marquee { width: 320px; overflow: hidden; white-space: nowrap; border: 3px ridge #c0c0c0; background: #000; padding: .6rem 0; }\n    .marquee__track { display: inline-block; padding-left: 100%; color: #00ff00; font-weight: 700; animation: scroll var(--speed) linear infinite; }\n    .marquee:hover .marquee__track, .marquee:focus-within .marquee__track { animation-play-state: paused; }\n    @keyframes scroll { to { transform: translateX(-100%); } }\n    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .marquee__track { animation: none; padding-left: 1rem; } }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"marquee\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <span class=\"marquee__track\">★ Welcome to my homepage ★ Best viewed in 800x600 ★ Sign my guestbook! ★&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
